{"type":"message","id":"d33de08a","parentId":"94c909d8","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:48:30.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that there's a pipeline 2448034759 on `develop` that failed. But my push was to `fix/auth-registration-ui`, not to `develop`. The MR #47 is already merged (since it was merged into develop and shows as merged). The push I made to `fix/auth-registration-ui` should have triggered a new pipeline. But I don't see a new one in the list...\n\nWait - looking at the pipelines again, I notice that the `iid` values are strange. Pipeline 2448034759 has `iid: 47` which is the MR number, but it's on `ref: develop`. \n\nSo the develop branch is failing with my latest push. I need to check if there's a new pipeline triggered for my fix/auth-registration-ui branch, or if the push didn't trigger one automatically.\n\nLooking at the pipeline list, my latest commit `8547471` isn't showing up yet — the most recent one is `a8cf208` from the MR merge. My push should have triggered a pipeline for that branch, but GitLab might have already created one that hasn't populated in the list yet. Let me wait and refresh, or manually trigger the pipeline to be sure.\n\nActually, I see that pipeline 2448034759 on develop failed, which was the merge of my MR into develop — that's the one failing in staging. Since I just pushed my fix, the pipeline should re-trigger automatically. Let me check the MR status to see if a new pipeline was triggered for my fix branch.","thinkingSignature":"b248c47268450c3eacbf0d30adf59db292d69e0405ac06506bdd8e5d1437d581"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6puo6x9gce1m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe && git log --all --oneline --graph | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3556,"output":376,"cacheRead":61258,"cacheWrite":410,"tota