{"type":"message","id":"de3fbac6","parentId":"c61c930d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:03:28.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The remote BE is responding correctly - it returns 401 Unauthorized (not 404). This means the endpoint exists on the remote BE too.\n\nSo the 404 might be coming from somewhere else - maybe the FE is calling the wrong URL, or there's a network issue connecting to the remote server.\n\nActually wait - if the curl works, the server is up and the endpoint exists. The 404 in the browser might be because:1. The browser can't reach 103.253.21.139:5002 (firewall/network)\n2. The FE is calling localhost:5002 instead of the remote URL (NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL not loaded in browser)\n\n\n3. The 404 error might actually be from a different resource entirely\n\nLet me check the network tab to see what's actually being requested, and verify whether NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL is properly set in the deployed environment - if it's missing, the FE would default to localhost instead of the remote server.","thinkingSignature":"053f48831c94b52199238f6c4f4e9481f58c3b7ac779985cd11f14f932ee0bac"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n3jsuff6xqvb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://103.253.21.139:5002/api/v1/license-categories --connect-timeout 5 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":134,"output":270,"cacheRead":96508,"cacheWrite":474,"totalTokens":97386,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056601151,"responseId":"062bac1acdb8e89ca3ac4aa88a4f4020"}}
