{"type":"message","id":"585ad76a","parentId":"2191bac9","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:04:44.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no docker-compose.yml in the FE. The CI pulls the code and runs `docker compose` from the remote server. Let me check what's on the remote server. The docker-compose.yml might be on the remote server, not in the repo.\n\nActually, looking at the CI script: it pulls from GitLab and runs `docker compose up -d --build`. The docker-compose.yml must be on the remote server at `/root/qlhv/ahv-qlhv-fe/`.\n\nSo the FE repo doesn't have a docker-compose.yml. The CI deploys to the remote server which already has docker-compose.yml configured with the correct environment variables.\n\nOK, so the FE deployment is entirely on the remote server. \n\nThe docker-compose setup there probably handles the environment variables, so I need to check what's actually configured on the remote server.","thinkingSignature":"db84239a96884d3b8892166a0b45c0d175d6e2e14d28310eb39ad8c695fee14a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1rdkw8c759ec_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code} %{url_effective}\" http://103.253.21.139:5002/api/v1/students 2>&1","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":127,"output":245,"cacheRead":99768,"cacheWrite":676,"totalTokens":100816,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056676652,"responseId":"062bac6655106d4f1a6cbc02cb090fda"}}
