{"type":"message","id":"8099f531","parentId":"98c1d60e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:05:57.591Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`000` with exit code 7 means \"couldn't connect to host\" - port 8686 is not open on 103.253.21.139. So the frontend is calling port 8686 but nothing is listening there.\n\nLet me check if there's a docker-compose on the deployment server that might be using a different port.\n\nThe issue is: the deployed frontend is calling `http://103.253.21.139:8686/api/v1/license-categories` but nothing is running on port 8686. The backend is on port 5002.\n\nThis means the `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in the deployed environment is `http://103.253.21.139:8686/api/v1` instead of `http://103.253.21.139:5002/api/v1`.\n \nI need to locate where the API URL is configured for the deployment. The docker-compose setup at the deployment location likely has the wrong NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL variable, so I should check there to update it to the correct port.","thinkingSignature":"9a06c6e468ae20977907c618b8f91d61da39377e8eda8e0ca5bed431b8039eea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_no1iki4t2248_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep -E '8686|5002' && echo \"---\" && ps aux | grep -E 'docker|node|next' | grep -v grep | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":287,"cacheRead":99671,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99958,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056749022,"responseId":"062bacae0bf02e9ac650ac38d16c20e9"}}
