{"type":"message","id":"55cbd8de","parentId":"133d5713","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:28.128Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The lint failed because `eslint: not found`! This is a dependency issue - the CI didn't run `yarn install` before running `yarn lint`. The pipeline is missing the install step for the lint job.\n\nLooking at the `.gitlab-ci.yml`, I see:- `backend_install` - this might not be a standard stage- `backend_lint` - runs `yarn lint` without `yarn install`- `backend_test` - runs `yarn test`\n\nThe lint job is failing because `eslint` is not installed. This is likely because the lint job uses `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` but the `node_modules` are cached but not including eslint (perhaps the yarn.lock was updated but the cache wasn't).\n\n\nI need to look at the CI configuration to see if the install step is properly defined for the lint job.","thinkingSignature":"d6f648440509b74205c555d795678760a60a90326a15a4bb96054b8a07201280"},{"type":"text","text":"Lỗi lint: `eslint: not found` — thiếu `yarn install` trước lint. Fix ngay:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i370f7w99t5i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '17,35p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/.gitlab-ci.yml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1248,"output":259,"cacheRead":117304,"cacheWrite":337,"totalTokens":119148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776057794756,"responseId":"062bb0c468d3f8abb0836516b6a743e8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d7bbc11","parentId":"55cbd8de","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:28.908Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i370f7w99t5i_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- .yarn-cache/\n    - node_modules/\n\n# Stage: Lint\nbackend_lint:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: lint\n  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn lint\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == \"merge_request_event\"\n\n# Stage: Test\nbackend_test:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: test"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":570,"aggregated":"- .yarn-cache/\n    - node_modules/\n\n# Stage: Lint\nbackend_lint:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: lint\n  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn lint\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == \"merge_request_event\"\n\n# Stage: Test\nbackend_test:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: test","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776057808816}}
{"type":"message","id":"0cc3b316","parentId":"6d7bbc11","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:37.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The lint job does have `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` before `yarn lint`. But `eslint` is not found. This might be because:1. The `node_modules` are being restored from cache but eslint was updated in yarn.lock and the cache doesn't have the new version\n2. Or `eslint` might not be a direct dependency in package.json\n\nLet me check if eslint is in the devDependencies.Actually, looking at the error more carefully: `eslint: not found` after `yarn install`. This means eslint is either:1. Not in package.json\n2. The frozen-lockfile install is failing silently\n\n\n3. Or the dependency isn't being installed correctly\n\nSince ESLint wasn't explicitly added before, it might just not be in the dependencies at all. Let me verify what's actually in the package.json.","thinkingSignature":"63aaf56c228dd74421c289c710fc225b0ccf3136df384a4f4c941a0f682ed6a9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lbf6ifsvezwr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -i \"eslint\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/package.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":223,"output":225,"cacheRead":117508,"cacheWrite":1535,"totalTokens":119491,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776057808922,"responseId":"062bb0d25a2b575a68916f5d7104239f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"403354ca","parentId":"0cc3b316","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:38.221Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lbf6ifsvezwr_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"lint\": \"eslint 'src/**/*.ts' --no-warn-ignored\",\n    \"@eslint/js\": \"^10.0.1\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^10.1.0\",\n    \"typescript-eslint\": \"^8.58.0\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":47,"aggregated":"\"lint\": \"eslint 'src/**/*.ts' --no-warn-ignored\",\n    \"@eslint/js\": \"^10.0.1\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^10.1.0\",\n    \"typescript-eslint\": \"^8.58.0\"","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776057818048}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a7e026a","parentId":"403354ca","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:47.092Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ESLint is in devDependencies. The issue is that the CI cache has old `node_modules` without eslint, and the `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` might not be properly installing eslint.\n\nThe issue is that `backend_lint` runs `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` which uses the cache, but the cache might have stale `node_modules`. \n\nActually, looking at the log: \"Successfully extracted cache\" - so the cache was extracted, but eslint is still not found. This might mean the cache has old node_modules without eslint.\n\nOne fix: clear the cache and re-run. But I can't do that from the CI.Let me re-think. \n\nThe `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` command is likely failing silently even though it exits with code 0, or the cache restoration is overwriting the freshly installed node_modules with stale versions. The most straightforward solution would be to skip the cache entirely or bust it, but I'm realizing the CI script itself might not be properly installing eslint in the first place.","thinkingSignature":"a7851938e0497adc521b7a95e1e8740d99f25d51adca3e3d2641dcd63cae6b0f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8zwlhpdrq993_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,40p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/.gitlab-ci.yml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":171,"output":273,"cacheRead":118779,"cacheWrite":607,"totalTokens":119830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776057818236,"responseId":"062bb0db75dd47c2c32cfb37d42dfa64"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e92b16e","parentId":"1a7e026a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:47.494Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8zwlhpdrq993_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"image: node:20-alpine\n\nvariables:\n  PRJ_PATH: \"/root/qlhv/ahv-qlhv-be\"\n  DOCKER_BUILDKIT: 1\n\nstages:\n  - lint\n  - test\n  - deploy\n\ncache:\n  key:\n    files:\n      - yarn.lock\n  paths:\n    - .yarn-cache/\n    - node_modules/\n\n# Stage: Lint\nbackend_lint:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: lint\n  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn lint\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == \"merge_request_event\"\n\n# Stage: Test\nbackend_test:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: test\n  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn test --passWithNoTests\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == \"merge_request_event\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":122,"aggregated":"image: node:20-alpine\n\nvariables:\n  PRJ_PATH: \"/root/qlhv/ahv-qlhv-be\"\n  DOCKER_BUILDKIT: 1\n\nstages:\n  - lint\n  - test\n  - deploy\n\ncache:\n  key:\n    files:\n      - yarn.lock\n  paths:\n    - .yarn-cache/\n    - node_modules/\n\n# Stage: Lint\nbackend_lint:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: lint\n  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn lint\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == \"merge_request_event\"\n\n# Stage: Test\nbackend_test:\n  tags:\n    - ahv-dtlx\n  stage: test\n  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn test --passWithNoTests\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == \"merge_request_event\"","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776057827388}}
{"type":"message","id":"22b054d6","parentId":"4e92b16e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:23:58.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The lint job does run `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` first. But it's using the `--cache-folder .yarn-cache` flag which stores the yarn cache, not `node_modules`. And then `node_modules` is also cached in the global cache. \n\nThe issue is: the CI cache has stale `node_modules` (without eslint). When `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` runs, it checks if `node_modules` exists and is valid, and might skip installing if it thinks it's up-to-date. But the frozen-lockfile should prevent that...\n\nActually, the real problem might be that `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` in the lint job doesn't restore from the cache properly - it uses the cache key based on yarn.lock, but then doesn't install because it thinks node_modules is fine.\n \nI think the lint job is pulling `node_modules` from the global cache, but the cached version predates when eslint was added to package.json, so the outdated modules are being used. Since I can't directly clear the cache through GitLab CI, I need to either add a `--check-files` flag to force yarn to verify all dependencies are actually installed, or modify the script to always reinstall rather than relying on the cache. --offline` option to prevent using cached packages, or try a completely fresh install with `--no-cache`. Since I can't clear the cache directly through the API, I'd need to either modify the CI script to force a fresh install, wait for the cache to naturally expire, or trigger a pipeline retry with a dummy change. Let me check if the GitLab API exposes a way to invalidate the cache, otherwise I might just need to create a dummy commit to retry the pipeline.","thinkingSignature":"f87f224abe01e2c886938afb911b202737f9ccb86ed9f6e48e8e45cff1bd5af7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yjv4h84h2aj5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/81078323/jobs/13887798497\" -H \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; j=json.load(sys.stdin); print('Status:', j['status']); print('Duration:', j.get('duration', 'N/A'))\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":344,"output":500,"cacheRead":119156,"cacheWrite":569,"totalTokens":120569,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776057827535,"responseId":"062bb0e58606110238349f87aeab1762"}}
