{"type":"message","id":"a1fb8d2c","parentId":"0b169d10","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:59:35.385Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat message. I already identified the JWT bug - `doc.id` vs `doc._id`. Looking at the code I found, the source file actually uses `doc._id` correctly. But the subagent said `doc.id` is undefined in `lean` docs.\n\nLet me check if there's a different place where `doc.id` is used, or if the subagent is looking at the compiled `dist` file incorrectly. The dist file also shows `doc._id`. \n\nMaybe the subagent was looking at the wrong file, or the issue is in the token payload extraction from a mongoose lean query where the result has `.id` but not `._id`.\n\n\nActually, I'm realizing the subagent flagged this as a blocker but I haven't found any actual code using `doc.id` in the DTLX codebase - the auth controller and token service both reference `doc._id`. This could be a false alarm, or the issue is in a compiled JavaScript file where the compiled code shows `doc._id` while the original TypeScript is correct.\n\nLet me look at the auth service to see if that's where the real problem lies.","thinkingSignature":"ac906ad70f15e374c4cd5f1e0985e99f4db59cfc38f8f99d8700767e471d60ab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wxn5uqrcodfh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"doc\\.\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/modules/auth/auth.service.ts | head -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":310,"cacheRead":15058,"cacheWrite":58272,"totalTokens":73640,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776142765430,"responseId":"062cfcaec1516d033c7d434860390b66"}}
