{"type":"message","id":"3f579498","parentId":"4083eb06","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:06:20.256Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The admin account is configured via env vars. The issue is that `admin2@gmail.com` was created separately without a role assigned. The proper fix is to:\n\n1. Add a seed for admin2 in the `initSeedData.ts`2. Or create a script to assign the admin role to admin2\n\nSince I can't run MongoDB directly, let me add a proper seed for admin2 in the initSeedData.ts, and also check if there's a migration that can be run.\n\nActually, looking at the initSystemAdminAccount function - it checks if admin users exist by looking at `userRolesService.getUsersByRoleId(adminRoleId)`. If there are users with admin role, it returns them. \n\nIf there are no admin users, it creates the system admin. The problem is likely that admin2 was created directly in MongoDB or by a separate seed without going through this initialization process, so it never got assigned a role. I should add a separate initialization function for admin2 that either creates the user if it doesn't exist or assigns the admin role if it does.","thinkingSignature":"83e152ec67b2887598847d0d3d1c90e74e25fb9dbdb79d8771c109294aa904ee"},{"type":"text","text":"**Vấn đề:** `admin2@gmail.com` được tạo riêng, không qua seed → không có `role_id` trong collection `userRoles`.\n\nFix bằng cách thêm hàm seed cho admin2:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wz5eq6due0cg_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/migration/initSeedData.ts","offset":1,"limit":25}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":143,"output":349,"cacheRead":82016,"cacheWrite":1806,"totalTokens":84314,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776150369628,"responseId":"062d1a62d7437d34d2411240a0654201"}}
