{"type":"message","id":"98cfcb70","parentId":"93683e07","timestamp":"2026-04-15T09:38:11.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both confluence servers use the same credentials and base URL. The only difference is the name. To access ALL spaces, the `CONF_DEFAULT_SPACE` restriction needs to be removed, or a new server config without it needs to be created.\n\nLooking at the confluence-mcp-server documentation, `CONF_DEFAULT_SPACE` is an optional environment variable that restricts access to a specific space. If we remove it, the server should be able to access all spaces.\n\nLet me update the config to remove the space restriction from at least one of the confluence servers, or create a new generic one.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the `confluence-mcp-server` might support `CONF_DEFAULT_SPACE` as optional. \n\nIf it's not set, the server should allow access to all spaces. I could either update both existing configs to remove the space restriction, or create a third server entry that doesn't specify a default space at all, keeping the space-restricted versions for backward compatibility.","thinkingSignature":"f57047aa30a56542e0958b3270576fed09f774ceeaa51ae627e61a2f32491d8f"},{"type":"text","text":"Tìm thấy config rồi. Để access ALL spaces, cần xóa `CONF_DEFAULT_SPACE` restriction. Thêm server mới không giới hạn:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kvs0kif9ctg7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":566,"output":266,"cacheRead":113139,"cacheWrite":539,"totalTokens":114510,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776245881468,"responseId":"062e8f7b2c0dc7ca9c18b9d07cf78723"}}
